title: Contraceptive prevalence, any methods (% of women ages 15-49)
name: sp.dyn.conu.zs
readme: Contraceptive prevalence rate is the percentage of women who are practicing, or whose sexual partners are practicing, any form of contraception. It is usually measured for women ages 15-49 who are married or in union.
